@NODE Main "FREEMEM"
@TOC "rexx.guide/APPENDIX D"
@{b}FREEMEM()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}FREEMEM(address, length)@{ub}

Releases a block of memory of the given length to the system freelist. The
address parameter is a four-byte string, typically obtained by a prior call to
@{"ALLOCMEM()" LINK "ALLOCMEM/main"}. FREEMEM() cannot be used to release memory allocated using
@{"GETSPACE()" LINK "GETSPACE/main"}, the ARexx internal memory allocator. The returned value is a boolean
success flag.

See also: @{"ALLOCMEM()" LINK "ALLOCMEM/main"}

Example:
@{fg shine}
        say freemem('00042000'x,32)     ==>1
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
